Forbidden anti-patterns:

Architecture:
- Anemic Domain Model
- God Service
- Shared mutable state
- Circular dependencies

Code:
- Boolean flags controlling behavior
- Large if/else chains instead of polymorphism
- Magic numbers or strings
- Copy-paste logic

DDD violations:
- Repositories returning ORM entities
- Domain depending on infrastructure
- Business logic in controllers

Process:
- Premature abstraction
- Framework-driven design
- Over-engineering MVP paths

If any anti-pattern appears:
- Stop
- Refactor
- Explain why the change improves the system
